## Learn More

Cardano epochs are one of the core components of the network's staking system, coordinating reward calculations, stake snapshots, delegation updates, and block production across every 5-day cycle.

Understanding how epochs work can help ADA holders better understand reward timing, delegation changes, and the overall operation of Cardano's proof-of-stake infrastructure.

For the complete Cardano Epoch Calendar 2026, including detailed epoch dates and additional staking information, visit:

